0:12:46.26,000 --> 0:12:48,000
if the places where I'd been born

313
0:12:48.26,000 --> 0:12:5,000
and gone to school

314
0:12:50.26,000 --> 0:12:52,000
and got married,

315
0:12:52.26,000 --> 0:12:54,000
if all those places were just going to disappear forever.

316
0:12:54.26,000 --> 0:12:56,000
How, literally, ungrounded

317
0:12:56.26,000 --> 0:12:58,000
that would make me feel.

318
0:13:00.26,000 --> 0:13:03,000
Very shortly, I'll be setting out to try and get to Australia,

319
0:13:03.26,000 --> 0:13:06,000
and if I'm successful, I'll be the first woman ever to row solo

320
0:13:06.26,000 --> 0:13:08,000
all the way across the Pacific.

321
0:13:08.26,000 --> 0:13:11,000
And I try to use this to bring awareness to these environmental issues,

322
0:13:11.26,000 --> 0:13:14,000
to bring a human face to the ocean.

323
0:13:14.26,000 --> 0:13:17,000
If the Atlantic was about my inner journey,

324
0:13:17.26,000 --> 0:13:19,000
discovering my own capabilities,

325
0:13:19.26,000 --> 0:13:22,000
maybe the Pacific has been about my outer journey,

326
0:13:22.26,000 --> 0:13:24,000
figuring out how I can use

327
0:13:24.26,000 --> 0:13:26,000
my interesting career choice

328
0:13:26.26,000 --> 0:13:29,000
to be of service to the world,

329
0:13:29.26,000 --> 0:13:32,000
and to take some of those things that I've learned out there

330
0:13:32.26,000 --> 0:13:34,000
and apply them to the situation

331
0:13:34.26,000 --> 0:13:37,000
that humankind now finds itself in.

332
0:13:37.26,000 --> 0:13:4,000
I think there are probably three key points here.

333
0:13:40.26,000 --> 0:13:42,000
The first one is about

334
0:13:42.26,000 --> 0:13:44,000
the stories that we tell ourselves.

335
0:13:44.26,000 --> 0:13:46,000
For so long, I told myself

336
0:13:46.26,000 --> 0:13:48,000
that I couldn't have an adventure

337
0:13:48.26,000 --> 0:13:5,000
because I wasn't six foot tall

338
0:13:50.26,000 --> 0:13:53,000
and athletic and bearded.

339
0:13:53.26,000 --> 0:13:56,000
And then that story changed.

340
0:13:56.26,000 --> 0:13:59,000
I found out that people had rowed across oceans.

341
0:13:59.26,000 --> 0:14:02,000
I even met one of them and she was just about my size.

342
0:14:02.26,000 --> 0:14:04,000
So even though I didn't grow any taller,

343
0:14:04.26,000 --> 0:14:06,000
I didn't sprout a beard,

344
0:14:06.26,000 --> 0:14:09,000
something had changed: My interior dialogue had changed.

345
0:14:09.26,000 --> 0:14:12,000
At the moment, the story that we collectively tell ourselves

346
0:14:12.26,000 --> 0:14:14,000
is that we need all this stuff,

347
0:14:14.26,000 --> 0:14:16,000
that we need oil.

348
0:14:16.26,000 --> 0:14:19,000
But what about if we just change that story?

349
0:14:19.26,000 --> 0:14:21,000
We do have alternatives,

350
0:14:21.26,000 --> 0:14:23,000
and we have the power of free will

351
0:14:23.26,000 --> 0:14:26,000
to choose those alternatives, those sustainable ones,

352
0:14:26.26,000 --> 0:14:28,000
to create a greener future.

353
0:14:30.26,000 --> 0:14:32,000
The second point is about

354
0:14:32.26,000 --> 0:14:34,000
the accumulation of tiny actions.

355
0:14:35.26,000 --> 0:14:38,000
We might think that anything that we do as an individual

356
0:14:38.26,000 --> 0:14:41,000
is just a drop in the ocean, that it can't really make a difference.

357
0:14:41.26,000 --> 0:14:43,000
But it does. Generally, we haven't

358
0:14:43.26,000 --> 0:14:46,000
got ourselves into this mess through big disasters.

359
0:14:46.26,000 --> 0:14:48,000
Yes, there have been the Exxon Valdezes

360
0:14:48.26,000 --> 0:14:5,000
and the Chernobyls,

361
0:14:50.26,000 --> 0:14:52,000
but mostly it's been an accumulation

362
0:14:52.26,000 --> 0:14:54,000
of bad decisions

363
0:14:54.26,000 --> 0:14:56,000
by billions of individuals,

364
0:14:56.26,000 --> 0:14:59,000
day after day and year after year.

365
0:14:59.26,000 --> 0:15:01,000
And, by the same token, we can turn that tide.

366
0:15:01.26,000 --> 0:15:03,000
We can start making better,

367
0:15:03.26,000 --> 0:15:06,000
wiser, more sustainable decisions.

368
0:15:06.26,000 --> 0:15:08,000
And when we do that, we're not just one person.

369
0:15:08.26,000 --> 0:15:11,000
Anything that we do spreads ripples.

370
0:15:11.26,000 --> 0:15:13,000
Other people will see if you're in the supermarket line

371
0:15:13.26,000 --> 0:15:15,000
and you pull out your

372
0:15:15.26,000 --> 0:15:17,000
reusable grocery bag.

373
0:15:17.26,000 --> 0:15:19,000
Maybe if we all start doing this,

374
0:15:19.26,000 --> 0:15:21,000
we can make it socially unacceptable

375
0:15:21.26,000 --> 0:15:24,000
to say yes to plastic in the checkout line.

376
0:15:24.26,000 --> 0:15:26,000
That's just one example.

377
0:15:26.26,000 --> 0:15:28,000
This is a world-wide community.

378
0:15:29.26,000 --> 0:15:31,000
The other point:

379
0:15:31.26,000 --> 0:15:33,000
It's about taking responsibility.

380
0:15:33.26,000 --> 0:15:35,000
For so much of my life,

381
0:15:35.26,000 --> 0:15:38,000
I wanted something else to make me happy.

382
0:15:38.26,000 --> 0:15:4,000
I thought if I had the right house or the right car

383
0:15:40.26,000 --> 0:15:42,000
or the right man in my life,

384
0:15:42.26,000 --> 0:15:44,000
then I could be happy.

385
0:15:44.26,000 --> 0:15:47,000
But when I wrote that obituary exercise,

386
0:15:47.26,000 --> 0:15:5,000
I actually grew up a little bit in that moment

387
0:15:50.26,000 --> 0:15:53,000
and realized that I needed to create my own future.

388
0:15:53.26,000 --> 0:15:55,000
I couldn't just wait passively

389
0:15:55.26,000 --> 0:15:58,000
for happiness to come and find me.

390
0:15:58.26,000 --> 0:16:,000
And I suppose I'm a selfish environmentalist.

391
0:16:00.26,000 --> 0:16:02,000
I plan on being around for a long time,

392
0:16:02.26,000 --> 0:16:04,000
and when I'm 90 years old,

393
0:16:04.26,000 --> 0:16:06,000
I want to be happy and healthy.

394
0:16:06.26,000 --> 0:16:08,000
And it's very difficult to be happy

395
0:16:08.26,000 --> 0:16:1,000
on a planet that's racked

396
0:16:10.26,000 --> 0:16:13,000
with famine and drought.

397
0:16:13.26,000 --> 0:16:15,000
It's very difficult to be healthy on a planet

398
0:16:15.26,000 --> 0:16:18,000
where we've poisoned the earth

399
0:16:18.26,000 --> 0:16:21,000
and the sea and the air.

